@TechMovesLogistics.Api_HostAddress = https://localhost:7216

### GET all contracts
GET {{TechMovesLogistics.Api_HostAddress}}/api/contracts
Accept: application/json

###

### GET contracts filtered by status
GET {{TechMovesLogistics.Api_HostAddress}}/api/contracts?status=Active
Accept: application/json

###

### POST create contract (use a valid clientId from your database)
POST {{TechMovesLogistics.Api_HostAddress}}/api/contracts
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "clientId": 1,
  "startDate": "2026-01-01",
  "endDate": "2026-12-31",
  "status": "Draft",
  "serviceLevel": "Premium Freight"
}

###

### PATCH update contract status (cannot test in browser address bar — use Send Request here)
PATCH {{TechMovesLogistics.Api_HostAddress}}/api/contracts/1/status
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "status": "Active"
}

###

### GET contract by id
GET {{TechMovesLogistics.Api_HostAddress}}/api/contracts/1
Accept: application/json

###

### PUT update contract
PUT {{TechMovesLogistics.Api_HostAddress}}/api/contracts/1
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "clientId": 1,
  "startDate": "2026-01-01",
  "endDate": "2026-12-31",
  "status": "Active",
  "serviceLevel": "Standard Freight"
}

###

### GET download contract PDF (works in browser after upload)
GET {{TechMovesLogistics.Api_HostAddress}}/api/contracts/1/agreement

###

### POST upload contract PDF — use Postman or curl (multipart/form-data)
# Postman: POST .../api/contracts/1/agreement → Body → form-data → key "file" (File) → pick .pdf
# PowerShell:
# curl.exe -X POST "{{TechMovesLogistics.Api_HostAddress}}/api/contracts/1/agreement" -F "file=@C:\path\to\agreement.pdf"

###

### DELETE contract (deletes linked PDF if present; cascades service requests)
DELETE {{TechMovesLogistics.Api_HostAddress}}/api/contracts/1

###

### GET all clients
GET {{TechMovesLogistics.Api_HostAddress}}/api/clients
Accept: application/json

###

### GET client by id
GET {{TechMovesLogistics.Api_HostAddress}}/api/clients/1
Accept: application/json

###

### POST create client
POST {{TechMovesLogistics.Api_HostAddress}}/api/clients
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Acme Logistics",
  "contactDetails": "admin@acme.com",
  "region": "Gauteng"
}

###

### PUT update client
PUT {{TechMovesLogistics.Api_HostAddress}}/api/clients/1
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Acme Logistics Updated",
  "contactDetails": "contact@acme.com",
  "region": "Western Cape"
}

###

### DELETE client (use an id with no linked contracts, or expect FK error)
DELETE {{TechMovesLogistics.Api_HostAddress}}/api/clients/1

###

### GET all service requests
GET {{TechMovesLogistics.Api_HostAddress}}/api/servicerequests
Accept: application/json

###

### GET service request by id
GET {{TechMovesLogistics.Api_HostAddress}}/api/servicerequests/1
Accept: application/json

###

### POST create service request (contract must be Active — not Expired/OnHold)
POST {{TechMovesLogistics.Api_HostAddress}}/api/servicerequests
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "contractId": 1,
  "description": "International freight shipment to Cape Town",
  "costUSD": 500.00,
  "status": "Pending"
}

###

### PUT update service request
PUT {{TechMovesLogistics.Api_HostAddress}}/api/servicerequests/1
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "contractId": 1,
  "description": "Updated shipment details",
  "costZAR": 9250.00,
  "costUSD": 500.00,
  "exchangeRateUsed": 18.50,
  "status": "InProgress"
}

###

### DELETE service request
DELETE {{TechMovesLogistics.Api_HostAddress}}/api/servicerequests/1

###
